  "original_title": "PM, other MPs express condolences on behalf of former Japanese PM Abe",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "PM, other MPs express condolences on behalf of former Japanese PM Abe",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "COLOMBO (News 1st); Prime Minister Ranil Wickremesinghe has signed the\u00a0Book of Condolences at the Japanese Embassy in Sri Lanka, expressing\u00a0his condolences on the death of the former Prime Minister of Japan, Shinzo Abe.",
        "The Minister of Public Administration, Home Affairs, Provincial Councils and Local Government and Leader of the House of Parliament, Dinesh Gunawardena too, signed the book of condolences placed at the Japanese Embassy.",
        "Moreover, the Ministry of Public Administration, Home Affairs, Provincial Councils and Local Government declared July 12th as a day of national mourning in Sri Lanka as a mark of respect for the former Japanese Prime Minister Shinzo Abe who was assassinated.",
        "The former Prime Minister of Japan Shinzo Abe was shot dead on 08th July while delivering a speech in Nara, Japan.",
        "PM, other MPs express condolences on behalf of former Japanese PM Abe"
      ],
